### 2.2 Registration form validation (fully functional)

| Username not blank, ≥ 4 chars | `if (username === '') …` |
| Username ≥ 2 unique chars | `uniqueCharCount(username) < 2` |
| No whitespace | `/\s/.test(username)` |
| No special characters | `/[^a-zA-Z0-9]/.test(username)` |
| Username must be unique | `users.some(u => u.username === username)` |
| Email not blank & valid format | HTML `required` + `type="email"`; extra check `if (email === '')` |
| Email not from `example.com` | `email.includes('example.com')` |
| Password ≥ 12 chars | `if (password1.length < 12)` |
| Upper‑case & lower‑case | `!/[a-z]/.test(pwd) || !/[A-Z]/.test(pwd)` |
| At least one number | `/[0-9]/.test(pwd)` |
| At least one special char | `/[!@#$%^&*(),.?":{}|<>]/.test(pwd)` |
| No “password” word | `/password/i.test(pwd)` |
| No username inside password | `pwd.toLowerCase().includes(username)` |
| Passwords match | `pwd !== pwd2` |
| Terms accepted | `if (!terms) …` |
| **Success flow** | `users.push({username,email,password:pwd}); setUsers(users); registerForm.reset(); alert('Registration successful!');` |

All error messages appear in the `<div id="errorDisplay">`.



